(i) The total number of shares that the State bank or trust company
has authority to issue;
(ii) The par value of the shares, which may not be less than $10 a
share; and
(iii) The total par value of all shares; AND
(8) FOR A NONDEPOSITORY TRUST COMPANY THAT INTENDS TO SEEK
THE COMMISSIONER’S AUTHORIZATION TO ENGAGE IN BUSINESS UNDER TITLE 14
OF THIS ARTICLE:
(I) A DISCLOSURE THAT THE NONDEPOSITORY TRUST
COMPANY WILL SEEK THE REQUIRED AUTHORIZATION FROM THE COMMISSIONER;
AND
